# Daily Culture Bot - Email Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your SMTP settings

# SMTP Server Configuration
# For Gmail (TLS on port 587)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password
SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=your-email@gmail.com

# For Siteground (SSL on port 465)
# SMTP_HOST=mail.yourdomain.com
# SMTP_PORT=465
# SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@yourdomain.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your-email-password
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=your-email@yourdomain.com

# For Outlook/Hotmail (TLS on port 587)
# SMTP_HOST=smtp-mail.outlook.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@outlook.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your-password
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=your-email@outlook.com

# For Yahoo (TLS on port 587)
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.mail.yahoo.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@yahoo.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password
# SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=your-email@yahoo.com

# Gmail Setup Instructions:
# 1. Enable 2-Factor Authentication in your Google Account
# 2. Generate an App Password for "Mail"
# 3. Use the App Password (not your regular password) in SMTP_PASSWORD
# 4. Keep 2FA enabled for security

# GitHub Actions Setup:
# Add these as GitHub Secrets in your repository:
# - SMTP_HOST
# - SMTP_PORT  
# - SMTP_USERNAME
# - SMTP_PASSWORD
# - SMTP_FROM_EMAIL
# - EMAIL_RECIPIENT (the email address to send daily emails to)
